<script>
(adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});
</script></p>

<p><img src="/assets/img/firefox/tcharaaamm.png" alt="Markdown rendering in Firefox" /></p>

<p>You can still customize the CSS to make it the way you want, centralized, for example as I did and is in the image, by going to:</p>

<p><strong>☰ → Extensions → … (from plugin) → Preferences → Preferences (from plugin)</strong></p>

<p>And below the field to insert your CSS, in my case I inserted: <code class="highlighter-rouge">body {max-width: 1000px; margin: auto; }</code> as in the image below:</p>

<p><img src="/assets/img/firefox/three dots" alt="three dots" />.png)
<img src="/assets/img/firefox/css.png" alt="css" /></p>

<p>Easy, right ?! ☺</p>
